t und u.a. in den unterschiedlichen Zugängen zum Koran begründet.  aStudying the Koran is not only a central interest of Muslim erudition but also important in order to understand the intellectual-religious backgrounds of the various - fundamentalist, liberal, traditional and modern positions - within the Islam. This book discusses the textual hermeneutic approaches in different regions of the Islam - from Turkey, Egypt, Syria and Iran to India. The contributions outline the Koran exegesis as mix-and-match hermeneutics various players with different interests, methodical approaches and life experiences participate in. This way the plurality in Islamic thinking and acting is taken for granted, one of its reasons being the different approaches to the Koran.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aHermeneutik. 4aIslamwissenschaft. 4aKoran. 4aKoranexegese. 4aReligionsgeschichte. 4aTafsir. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh  aHermeneutics.  aHistory of Religion.  aIslamic Studies.  aQuran.  aQuranic Exegesis.  aTafsir.1 aHundhammer, Marianus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlausing, Kathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNekroumi, Mohammed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoya, Abbas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoya, Abbas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSağır, Fatma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeker, Nimet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuleiman, Farid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package